Name: vaginal benign neoplasm
Definition: A female reproductive organ benign neoplasm that is located_in the vagina.

Name: vaginal cancer
Definition: A female reproductive system cancer that is located_in the vagina.

Name: obsolete cerebral amebiasis
Definition: An amebiasis that involves infection of the brain caused by the parasite Entamoeba histolytica resulting in brain abscesses.

Name: vaginitis
Definition: A vaginal disease that is characterized by inflammation of the vagina.

Name: obsolete malignant eyelid tumor
Definition: A vaginal disease that is characterized by inflammation of the vagina.

Name: vaginal discharge
Definition: A vaginal disease that is characterized by the presence of discharge.

Name: leukoplakia of vagina
Definition: A vaginal disease that is a precancerous lesion that is characterized by the presence of white plaques which cannot be rubbed off. Histology shows increased keratin.
